{
  "texts": [
    "Few-shot prompting can be done by adding some examples or explanations to the input depending on the complexity and variability of the task.",
    "Few-shot prompting can enhance accuracy by providing limited context that aids complex scenario understanding.",
    "The improvement is more pronounced compared to simple prefix and cloze prompts, which had lower accuracy in most of the tasks. 5.",
    "Ensemble approaches can also improve the performance of LLMs by combining outputs from multiple prompts using majority voting.",
    "Ensemble approaches can leverage the strengths of each prompt type and reduce the errors of individual prompts."
  ]
}